[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "So take a moment and let that sinking in we know so little that we understand 0% of what there is to know.  And no matter how much you learn that is always an "
      },
      {
        "text": "infinite",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " amount more that you don't know."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "..."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Ok glad you let that sink in because it is about to get worse."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Time - Taking Uncertainty to 11"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "AlignCenter",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "So if our understanding is already 0 how can it get worse? Well enter hour good friend time which take everything we know and roll dice to make sure some of that stuff goes from know things to unknown things.  "
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "But if I know nothing how can I ever make a decision? "
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Assume away Uncertainty"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Let's just attack the denominator, if I just assume somethings that will lower the \"Thing to Know\" small enough that I might be able to know something.  We often do this when we want to estimate something.  "
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Understanding is then easily defined as the percent of \"Things to Know\" that are \"Known Things\"."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Just to put a bow how little we understand, because \"Things to Know\" are infinite and Know Things\" are finite it follows \"Unknown Things\" are also infinite! So it does not matter how much we learn we will always know less then we don't know."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "As the Known things are finite, but there is no limit on the things to know, the only conclusion is our understanding is appoximently  0%."
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Then we will complete the project on May 15th."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Let start by looking at \"Things to know\", this is the sum of all of the \"Known Things\" and all of the \"Unknown Things\".  "
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "H1",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Embracing Uncertainty or \"You Know Nothing Erik Summerfield\""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "I was pondering how much I know and don't know and how they should affect how I make decisions. I have been a pusher of uncertainty (just see my blog post "
      },
      {
        "data": {
          "openModal": true,
          "slatenode": {
            "href": "https://www.phase2technology.com/blog/estimate-pirate-use-old"
          }
        },
        "type": "Link",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "Estimate like a Pirate use a B.O.A.T"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": ") and thought maybe if I do the math it would be a good way to show people that they should be less certain then they are.  Well, I found that in fact, I was being "
      },
      {
        "text": "too",
        "Bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " certain, and actually, "
      },
      {
        "text": "I know ",
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": "nothing",
        "Bold": true,
        "Italic": true
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "H2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "The Basic Math of Uncertainty "
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Assuming that the design will match the requirements and"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Assuming there is not a block that comes up that we do not know about yet"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Assuming we well have the developers that need and"
      }
    ]
  }
]

[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Assuming the client gets us requirements by Jan 8 and"
      }
    ]
  }
]

